comment: It’s 2019 & still the best show ever made.
"When the time comes for me to pick up a firearm, all will truly be lost." - Finch -

Everyone dies alone. But if you mean something to someone…
if you help someone or love someone, and even a single person
remembers you… then maybe you never really die at all?
 :''''''' (

You know, in the end, the Machine proved to have something that Samaritan didn't or couldn't have, and that is life experience or, most importantly, she didn't have all the luxuries that Samaritan enjoyed. Samaritan was "raised" like a spoiled child and in the face of a true contest where, alone, it would have to improvise for itself, the Machine, which always ran on shortage of time and resources and managed to live that way, she prevailed. In other words, Root's words, she had learned how to push back in the playground. And that's why she won.
Number 1 show of all time nothing better than poi
